						               													<description>Barbarians recreates the situation along the Rhine-Danube frontier of the Roman Empire in the years 70 BC to 260 AD.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 32 scenarios which can be played solitaire or by 2 players. Some scenarios can be adapted for play by 3 or 4 players. Scenarios range in playing time from 2 to 20 hours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It has an 8 page rulebook and is a straight forward UGO/IGO hex and counter war game. It is very much the unofficial expansion to Caesar's Legions. The rules are 99% similar to Caesar's Legions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Enemies of Rome depicted in the game include Roman Rebels, Germans, Britons, Pannonians, Gauls, Batavii, Sarmations (Roxolanni and Iazyges), Goths, Vandals, Bastarnae and Dacians.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the Designer Notes Keith Poulter acknowledges:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;The point of departure for the design was a fine game originally published under the title Eagles, and subsequently by Avalon Hill as Caesar's Legions.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the Designer Notes Keith Poulter asked for feedback on the game as:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Such feedback will be valuable, as we planned multi-scenario expansion kits (7 additional maps in all) covering western and southern Gaul, Spain, and Britain.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These expansions were never published.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, a related game (by different designers) using the Caeser's Legions system is Caesar in Gaul.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
